Muddu Bidda (Telugu is a 1956 drama film directed and produced by K. B. Tilak. 
It is a debut film for Tilak under the banner Anupama Films.
It was remade into the Hindi language as Chhoti Bahu in 1971, directed by K. B. Tilak himself.
